{"serial": "12014", "department_serial": 11, "code": "EL2077", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Presentation & Communication II", "ch": "演說與溝通II"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Amie Parry"], "ch": ["白瑞梅"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 3, "session": ["2", "3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "A", "room": "108"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 20, "department": {"ch": "英美語文學系", "en": "Department of English"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 38, "selected": 0, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "The objective of this course is to develop students’ fluency and lexical accuracy in English-speaking professional and academic contexts. It gives students a forum in which to make speculative, analytical statements and raise informed, helpful questions. The main goal is to come out of the course with experience and proficiency in a range of public speech tasks, from impromptu response to prepared formal presentation.", "en": "The objective of this course is to develop students’ fluency and lexical accuracy in English-speaking professional and academic contexts. It gives students a forum in which to make speculative, analytical statements and raise informed, helpful questions. The main goal is to come out of the course with experience and proficiency in a range of public speech tasks, from impromptu response to prepared formal presentation."}, "outline": {"ch": "Our topic this semester is doppelgangers. We begin with assigned short readings to introduce the topic and provide a critical framework for our class discussions. Ensuing class activities are based on film and television doppelganger narratives. Before each screening, students will be given handouts that introduce vocabulary and provide relevant historical and cultural background as well as note-taking sheets and/or discussion questions. Following each screening, students hold their own discussions in pairs or groups and then report back to the class. The midterm consists of presentations in teams of two followed by a Q＆A period. The final exam will be an individual presentation on a doppelganger narrative of your choice, which you introduce to the class and analyze with the critical frameworks from our readings. The final presentation will also be followed by a Q＆A period. The ability to field questions will be factored into presentation grades.", "en": "Our topic this semester is doppelgangers. We begin with assigned short readings to introduce the topic and provide a critical framework for our class discussions. Ensuing class activities are based on film and television doppelganger narratives. Before each screening, students will be given handouts that introduce vocabulary and provide relevant historical and cultural background as well as note-taking sheets and/or discussion questions. Following each screening, students hold their own discussions in pairs or groups and then report back to the class. The midterm consists of presentations in teams of two followed by a Q＆A period. The final exam will be an individual presentation on a doppelganger narrative of your choice, which you introduce to the class and analyze with the critical frameworks from our readings. The final presentation will also be followed by a Q＆A period. The ability to field questions will be factored into presentation grades."}, "textbook": {"ch": "Handouts provided by instructor; films screened in the classroom", "en": "Handouts provided by instructor; films screened in the classroom"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100%", "en": "100%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "其他", "en": ["Others"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "Course Grading  Policy: All conversation in this course will be conducted in English. Grades will be calculated according to students’ weekly participation (35％), midterms (30％), and the final presentation (35％). Attendance is mandatory.", "en": "Course Grading Policy: All conversation in this course will be conducted in English. Grades will be calculated according to students’ weekly participation (35％), midterms (30％), and the final presentation (35％). Attendance is mandatory."}, "officeHour": {"ch": "TBA", "en": "TBA"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "Students meet with the instructor individually or in groups.", "en": "Students meet with the instructor individually or in groups."}, "domain": {"ch": "語言訓練", "en": "語言訓練"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "英文閱讀解析與寫作論述", "rating": "(2)低", "assesments": ["實作/實驗"]}, {"competencies": "英語溝通與文化跨越", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "實作/實驗"]}, {"competencies": "審美欣賞與多元創意", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["實作/實驗"]}, {"competencies": "人文思維與社會關懷", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["實作/實驗"]}, {"competencies": "組織能力與人際合作", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["實作/實驗"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "English critical reading and analytical writing", "rating": "(2)Low", "assesments": ["Practices/Experiments"]}, {"competencies": "English oral communication and cultural crossing", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Practices/Experiments"]}, {"competencies": "aesthetic appreciation and creative diversity", "rating": "(3)Medium", "assesments": ["Practices/Experiments"]}, {"competencies": "humanities visions and social intervention", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Practices/Experiments"]}, {"competencies": "organizational ability and team work", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Practices/Experiments"]}]}, "assignCriteria": {"ch": ["系所:限英美語文學系。年級:限二年級。", "系所:限英美語文學系。", "系所:限輔系-英美語文學系、雙主修-英美語文學系。"], "en": ["Department:Department of English only.Year:Second Year only.", "Department:Department of English only.", "Department:Minor-English、Double Major-Department of English only."]}, "preselecStu": 0, "stuGender": {